core.conflict

Interface IConflictDomain<T,E>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of entities that define the conflict scope of a conflict domain.
    E - The type of entities that underly the conflict arising by a conflict source entity.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GeneralizationAdaptationAssociationClassVisitor, GeneralizationAdaptationAssociationVisitor, GeneralizationAdaptationAttributeVisitor, GeneralizationAdaptationClassAbstractVisitor, GeneralizationAdaptationDependencyVisitor

    public interface IConflictDomain<T,E>
    an IConflictDomain generic interface that defines a domain entity where conflicts might possibly arise during an operation execution. A conflict domain, for example, can designate a metamodeling transformation whose execution might give rise to a conflict, when a target entity end up owning two identical elements (e.g. having the same name).

    This interface provides operations for accessing the conflict domain's active conflict scope, active conflict candidate, active conflict strategy, and active conflict strategy type.

    It must be implemented by any concrete class designating a conflict domain.
    Author:
    Bachar Rima
    See Also:
    AbstractConflictScope, IConflictCandidate, AbstractConflictSource, AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy, IConflictResolutionStrategyType
